'''Alexandr Sojka''' (born 2 April 2003) is a Czech professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[FC Viktoria Plzeň|Viktoria Plzeň]] and the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic national team]]. His previous clubs include [[FC Hradec Králové|Hradec Králové]], who he played for in 2025, and [[FC Silon Táborsko|Táborsko]], where he spent a year and a half on loan from 2023 to 2024. He represented the Czech Republic at youth level, playing for his nation at the [[2025 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]], before making his debut for the senior side in 2026 and being nominated in the squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].

==Early life and family==
Sojka started playing football in [[Klatovy]] for [[SK Klatovy 1898]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Neumann |first1=Robert |last2=Bastlová |first2=Jarmila |title=Jako špunt si po historickém titulu odnesl reklamu. Oslavy chci zažít i jako hráč, říká plzeňský univerzál |url=https://www.sport.cz/clanek/fotbal-ceska-1-liga-jako-spunt-si-po-historickem-titulu-odnesl-reklamu-oslavy-chci-zazit-i-jako-hrac-rika-plzensky-univerzal-5412952 |access-date=2026-05-23 |work=Sport.cz |date=2026-03-05 |language=cs|publisher=Borgis}}</ref> His older brother, Jindřich Jr., is also a footballer, but never played in a professional league.<ref>{{cite news |last=Mangl |first=Martin |title=V rodinném souboji uspěl mladší ze Sojků. Hrál fakt dobře, uznal bratr Jindřich |url=https://klatovsky.denik.cz/fotbal_region/v-rodinnem-souboji-uspel-mladsi-ze-sojku-hral-fakt-dobre-uznal-bratr-jindrich-20.html |access-date=2026-05-23 |work=Deník |date=2022-02-07 |language=cs|publisher=Vltava Labe Media}}</ref> Their father, Jindřich Sojka Sr., was also a footballer<ref>{{cite news |last=Kanta |first=Tomáš |title=Klatovský fotbal slaví 120 let. Přijede mistrovská Viktoria Plzeň s pohárem |url=https://klatovsky.denik.cz/fotbal_region/klatovsky-fotbal-slavi-120-let-prijede-mistrovska-viktoria-plzen-s-poharem-20180617.html |access-date=2026-05-23 |work=Deník |date=2018-06-17 |language=cs|publisher=[[Vltava Labe Media]]}}</ref> and was the chairman of SK Klatovy from 2002 to 2024, Alexandr's entire childhood.<ref>{{cite news |last=Chmelová |first=Yvetta |title=Předseda Jindřich Sojka po sezoně končí. Jsem vyždímaný a ubíjí mne mezilidské vztahy v klubu, vysvětluje své rozhodnutí |url=https://www.fotbal-klatovy.cz/c/predseda-jindrich-sojka-po-sezone-konci-jsem-vyzdimany-a-ubiji-mne-mezilidske-vztahy-v-klubu-vysvetluje-sve-rozhodnuti-55 |access-date=2026-05-23 |publisher=SK Klatovy 1898 |date=2024-05-15 |language=cs}}</ref>

==Club career==
Sojka spent the second half of the 2022–23 season on loan at [[FC Silon Táborsko|Táborsko]] in the second-tier [[Czech National Football League]], scoring once for the club in 12 appearances. His loan was extended to include the whole of the following 2023–24 season.<ref name="denik23">{{cite news |last=Mangl |first=Martin |title=Sojka pokračuje v druholigovém Táborsku. Jsem rád, že to takhle dopadlo, řekl |url=https://klatovsky.denik.cz/fotbal_region/sojka-pokracuje-v-druholigovem-taborsku-jsem-rad-ze-to-takhle-dopadlo-rekl-20230.html |access-date=2026-05-22 |work=[[Deník]] |date=2023-06-26 |language=cs|publisher=Vltava Labe Media}}</ref> Sojka played 17 matches in the [[Czech First League]] for Viktoria Plzeň in the 2024–25 season, as well as making nine appearances in the [[UEFA Europa League]]. He moved to [[FC Hradec Králové|Hradec Králové]] on a permanent transfer after the season, with the announcement being made in June 2025.<ref name="denik25">{{cite news |last=Švec |first=Martin |title="Lvíče" Sojka přestoupil z Viktorie do Hradce. Míka jde na hostování do Prešova |url=https://klatovsky.denik.cz/fotbal-prvni-liga/lvice-sojka-prestoupil-z-viktorie-do-hradce-mika-jde-na-hostovani-do-presova-202.html |access-date=2026-05-22 |work=Deník |date=2025-06-26 |language=cs|publisher=Vltava Labe Media}}</ref> Sojka played for Hradec Králové in the first half of the [[2025–26 Czech First League]], playing in 18 of the club's 19 matches. He left after Plzeň activated a buy back clause in his contract, joining up with his former team in January 2026.<ref>{{cite news |title=Plzeň si koupila zpátky Sojku z Hradce, novým gólmanem je Ťapaj z Ružomberoku |url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/prvni-liga/alexandr-sojka-prestup-plzen-hradec-kralove.A260105_105017_fotbal_ten |access-date=2026-05-22 |work=[[iDNES.cz]]|date=2026-01-05 |language=cs|publisher=[[Mafra (company)|Mafra]]}}</ref>

==International career==
Having represented the Czech Republic four times at [[Czech Republic national under-21 football team|under-21 level]], Sojka was one of nine midfielders named in head coach [[Jan Suchopárek]]'s 24-man squad for the [[2025 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]] in May 2025.<ref>{{cite news |title=Na Euro do 21 let i s ostravským Šínem. Suchopárek nominoval také dva nováčky |url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/me-do-21-let/nominace-na-euro-u21-2025-jede-sin-i-dva-novacci.A250528_102424_fot_reprez_jic |access-date=2026-05-22 |work=iDNES.cz |date=2025-05-28 |language=cs|publisher=Mafra}}</ref> He played in the tournament.<ref name="denik25"/> Sojka received his first call-up for the senior [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic]] team in May 2026 for a friendly match against [[Kosovo national football team|Kosovo]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Jáša |first=Mikuláš |title=Kabongo, Sojka a Sochůrek. ‚Jestli se dostanou do užší nominace, bude to zázrak,‘ říká o nováčcích Siegl |url=https://www.irozhlas.cz/sport/fotbal/fotbal-ceska-fotbalova-reprezentace-nominace-matej-kovar-kabongo-sojka-sochurek_2605220919_ask |access-date=2026-05-22|work=iROZHLAS |publisher=[[Czech Radio]] |date=2026-05-22 |language=cs}}</ref> He made his debut in the match alongside two other players.<ref>{{cite news |title=Výhru nad Kosovem režíroval Hložek. Kuchta nedohrál, ale je v pořádku |url=https://sport.ceskatelevize.cz/clanek/fotbal/cesti-fotbaliste-nastoupi-proti-kosovu-se-tremi-debutanty-157123 |access-date=2026-06-04 |work=ČT Sport |publisher=[[Czech Television]] |date=2026-05-31 |language=cs}}</ref>

